wsit:clean

Full name:

com.github.wsitbt:wsit-maven-plugin:1.0.8-SNAPSHOT:clean

Description:

Strips wsit configuration from a file. The file must be a WSDL file.

Attributes:

  • Requires a Maven project to be executed.
  • Since version: 1.0.
  • Binds by default to the lifecycle phase: generate-resources.

Required Parameters

Name Type Since Description
file File 1.0 The file to strip WSIT configuration from. Must be a wsit configuration file (starts with the wsdl document element).

Optional Parameters

Name Type Since Description
todir File 1.0 The configuration files will be written to this directory. Either this or tofile must be specified.
tofile File 1.0 The configuration files will be written to this file. Either this or todir must be specified.

Parameter Details

file:

The file to strip WSIT configuration from. Must be a wsit configuration file (starts with the wsdl document element).
  • Type: java.io.File
  • Since: 1.0
  • Required: Yes
  • Expression: wsit-clean.file

todir:

The configuration files will be written to this directory. Either this or tofile must be specified.
  • Type: java.io.File
  • Since: 1.0
  • Required: No
  • Expression: wsit-clean.todir

tofile:

The configuration files will be written to this file. Either this or todir must be specified.
  • Type: java.io.File
  • Since: 1.0
  • Required: No
  • Expression: wsit-clean.tofile
